'''Tatsuya Tanaka''' (ç°ä¸­ éä¹, born November 27, 1982 in [[ShÅ«nan, Yamaguchi]]) is a [[Japan]]ese [[football (soccer)|football]]er and professional rehabiller who plays for [[Urawa Red Diamonds]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Guardian.co.uk]]|title=Stats Centre: Tatsuya Tanaka Facts|url=http://guardian.touch-line.com/StatsCentre.asp?Lang=0&CTID=63&CPID=147&pStr=Player&PLID=65745&TEID=3543|accessdate=2010-02-22}}</ref> He is a right-footed forward and an aggressive dribbler.
==Playing career==
When he was at ShÅ«yÅ Junior High School, he represented [[Yamaguchi Prefecture]] with future international teammate [[Seiichiro Maki]]. He went on to football powerhouse Teikyo High School. While at Teikyo, Tanaka was chosen as one of the Designated Players for Development by [[J. League]] and [[Japan Football Association|JFA]]. Because of this status, he was able to register as a [[FC Tokyo]] player while he was still eligible to play for his high school club.
After graduating Teikyo, he joined Urawa. His first league appearance came on April 29, 2001 against [[Kashima Antlers]]. His first professional goal came on May 21, 2001 against [[Tokyo Verdy 1969]].
He represented Japan at several underage levels. He was part of the [[Japan at the 2004 Summer Olympics#Football (Soccer)|Japanese 2004 Olympic football team]] eliminated in the first round after finishing fourth in group B, below group winners [[Paraguay]], [[Italy]], and [[Ghana]].
He made his international debut on July 31, 2005 in an [[East Asian Cup]] against [[North Korea national football team|North Korea]] when he replaced [[Keiji Tamada]] in the 67th minute. He scored his first international goal on August 3, 2005 against [[China national football team|China]] in the same tournament. His most recent goal came against Qatar on November 19, 2008.
